Psychological stress: As described above, against the background of the COVID-19 epidemic, many patients suffer from unforeseen severe stress because they often have to endure long quarantine periods, cope with high uncertainties and observe the deaths of their relatives and other patients.
To relieve the stress of such patients and to help them return to normal life, psychological consultations and long-term support must be provided.
